her%20than%20the%20wholesale%20price%20that%20prevailed%20on%20August%2019%20when%20the%20export%20duty%20was%20imposed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20this%20price%20point%2C%20export%20duty%20was%20neither%20expected%20nor%20warranted%20as%20the%20onion%20farmers%20had%20an%20opportunity%20of%20realising%20better%20prices%2C%20after%20suffering%20from%20low%20prices%20when%20they%20harvested%20Rabi%20onions.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20clear%20that%20Indian%20agriculture%20does%20not%20produce%20enough%20surpluses%20due%20to%20which%20government%20intervention%20will%20continue%20whenever%20prices%20rise%20to%20levels%20considered%20uncomfortable%20by%20the%20government%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20elections%20are%20near.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESiraj%20Hussain%20is%20a%20former%20Union%20agriculture%20secretary.%20Kriti%20Khurana%20is%20a%20PhD%20scholar%20of%20economics%20at%20BITS%20Pilani%2C%20Hyderabad.%20Views%20are%20personal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692873027000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14102358%2F5560910594_bdc7d1c175_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fonion-export-duty-farmers-surplus%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20clear%20that%20Indian%20agriculture%20does%20not%20produce%20enough%20surpluses%20due%20to%20which%20government%20intervention%20will%20continue%20whenever%20prices%20rise%20to%20levels%20considered%20uncomfortable%20by%20the%20government%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20elections%20are%20near.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fonion-export-duty-farmers-surplus%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Apple%20finally%20thinks%20you%20should%20be%20able%20to%20fix%20an%20iPhone%20or%20Mac%20yourself%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20four%20digit%20security%20code%20is%20entered%20on%20an%20Apple%20Iphone%20with%20splintered%20glass%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e72469a7adf7001906c957%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20broken%20iPhone.%3Cp%3EThomas%20Trutschel%2FPhotothek%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EApple%20spent%20years%20opposing%20bills%20that%20would%20give%20customers%20the%20right%20to%20repair%20their%20own%20devices.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20it's%20since%20changed%20tact.%20First%2C%20launching%20its%20self-service%20repair%20program%20in%20stores.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20it's%20supporting%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20require%20it%20provide%20tools%20and%20parts%20to%20consumers%20and%20repair%20shops.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20made%20a%20surprise%20move%20this%20week%20by%20endorsing%20a%20California%20bill%20that%20would%20give%20consumers%20the%20right%20to%20repair%20or%20modify%20their%20devices%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2023%2F08%2F23%2Fapple-lends-support-to-california-state-right-to-repair-bill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETechCrunch%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20wrote%20to%20Senator%20Susan%20Eggman%2C%20the%20bill's%20sponsor%2C%20to%20declare%20its%20support%20for%20the%20legislation%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleginfo.legislature.ca.gov%2Ffaces%2FbillNavClient.xhtml%3Fbill_id%3D202320240SB244%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESB%20244%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20would%20enact%20a%20statewide%20%26quot%3BRight%20to%20Repair%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20intends%20to%20%26quot%3Bprovide%20a%20fair%20marketplace%20for%20the%20repair%20of%20electronic%20and%20appliance%20products%20and%20to%20prohibit%20intentional%20barriers%20and%20limitations%20to%20third-party%20repair.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20it%20would%20give%20anyone%20who%20owns%20a%20device%20the%20legal%20right%20to%20repair%20or%20modify%20it%20%E2%80%94%20barring%20a%20few%20exceptions%20like%20game%20consoles.%20This%20means%20that%20manufacturers%20would%20be%20required%20to%20give%20customers%20and%20independent%20repair%20shops%20access%20to%20the%20appropriate%20tools%20and%20manuals%20to%20make%20repairs.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple's%20endorsement%20marks%20a%20pretty%20major%20change%20of%20direction.%20In%202017%2C%20the%20company%20was%20paying%20a%20lobbying%20firm%20to%20oppose%20New%20York's%20Right%20to%20Repair%20Act%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen%2Farticle%2Fnz85y7%2Fapple-is-lobbying-against-your-right-to-repair-iphones-new-york-state-records-confirm%3Fref%3D404media.co%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVice%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20earliest%20disputes%20at%20Apple%20involved%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20right%20to%20repair.%20Cofounder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-steve-wozniak-supports-users-right-to-repair-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESteve%20Wozniak%3C%2Fa%3E%20wanted%20its%20computers%20to%20have%20open%20systems%20that%20would%20let%20customers%20tinker%20with%20them%2C%20but%20Steve%20Jobs%20disagreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20has%20since%20become%20more%20open%2C%20launching%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fapple-self-service-repair%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eself-service%20repair%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202022%20that%20lets%20customers%20order%20parts%20and%20rent%20tools%20needed%20to%20fix%20their%20iPhones%20or%20Macs%20instead%20of%20replacing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20not%20only%20saves%20customers%20money%20but%20is%20also%20better%20for%20the%20environment%20because%20it%20helps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinside