ts.%20It's%20permanently%20remote.%20It's%20awesome.%20It's%20wonderful%2C%26quot%3B%20Done%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDone's%20story%20shows%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-life-balance-quiet-quitting-great-resignation-productivity-2023-8%5C%22%3Econtinued%20tension%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20how%20bosses%20think%20businesses%20should%20run%20and%20how%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-anywhere-but-office-coworking-gyms-2023-8%5C%22%3Eemployees%20want%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Workers%20have%20chafed%20at%20heavy-handed%20attempts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-work-from-home-employees-better-boss-managers-ceo-2022-6%5C%22%3Emicromanage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretire-return-to-office-baby-boomer-never-wants-go-back-2023-4%5C%22%3Efirms%20yanking%20their%20employees%20back%20in%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20strategy%20that%20might%20backfire%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-forever-boss-trust-employees-2023-8%5C%22%3Eemployers%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20Done%20says%20he's%20just%20as%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%20more%20%E2%80%94%20productive%20in%20a%20fully%20remote%20role%2C%20where%20he%20has%20the%20trust%20of%20his%20company%20to%20get%20his%20work%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20great%20remote%20work%20debate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20war%20over%20remote%20work%2C%20employers%20and%20employees%20alike%20have%20debated%20whether%20or%20not%20a%20mandatory%20return-to-office%20policy%20actually%20works.%20While%20some%20recent%20research%20has%20shown%20workers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwfh-work-from-home-decreases-productivity-18-percent-study-rto-2023-8%5C%22%3Emore%20productive%20at%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20other%20studies%20reveal%20workers%20may%20quit%20if%20companies%20mandate%20fully%20in-person%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20all%20comes%20down%20to%20trust%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0if%20you%20have%20faith%20your%20workers%20will%20get%20the%20job%20done%2C%20the%20work%20may%20get%20done%20more%20efficiently%20and%20effectively%20than%20micromanaging%20workers%20in%20an%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20really%20feel%20that%20you%20cannot%20trust%20the%20people%20you've%20hired%2C%20then%20maybe%20the%20best%20solution%20is%20for%20some%20type%20of%20oversight%20system%20where%20managers%20are%20walking%20around%20your%20desks%2C%26quot%3B%20Sam%20Eitzen%2C%20CEO%20of%20photo%20and%20video%20solutions%20company%20Snapbar%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-forever-boss-trust-employees-2023-8%5C%22%3Epreviously%20told%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20just%20think%20that%20for%20me%2C%20that%20doesn't%20seem%20like%20a%20great%20long-term%20solution.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStanford%20University%20economics%20professor%20Nicholas%20Bloom%20has%20reiterated%20that%20workers%20have%20kept%20up%20their%20productivity%20at%20home%2C%20citing%20data%20revealing%20the%20US%20is%20still%20on%20the%20pre-pandemic%20growth%20trend%20even%20with%20the%20number%20of%20remote%20workers%20quintupling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBloom%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20opportunities%20for%20constructive%20leisure%20at%20home%20are%20much%20higher%20than%20in%20an%20office%2C%20which%20has%20led%20workers%20to%20take%20more%20profound%20breaks%20or%20do%20workouts%20to%20keep%20their%20minds%20fresh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20studies%2C%20you%20see%20the%20valuation%20put%20on%20work%20from%20home%20is%20equivalent%20to%20about%20an%208%25%20pay%20increase%2C%20and%20the%20biggest%20driver%20of%20that%20is%20avoiding%20the%20commute%2C%20which%20is%20hardly%20surprising%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20second-biggest%20driver%20is%20flexibility%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20reflects%20the%20fact%20that%20breaks%20are%20just%20much%20more%20valuable%20at%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20businesses%20expect%20the%20current%20amount%20of%20remote%20work%20to%20continue%20into%20next%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20New%20York's%20most%20recent%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorkfed.org%2Fmedialibrary%2Fmedia%2FSurvey%2Fbusiness_leaders%2F2023%2F2023_08Supplemental.pdf%3Fsc_lang%3Den%26hash%3DEBCDE1519D854626BAE55AF3DA282BF0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmpire%20State%20Manufacturing%20Survey%20and%20Business%20Leaders%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%2017%25%20of%20service%20firms%20expect%20to%20require%20more%20in-person%20work%20next%20year%2C%20reporting%20declines%20in%20workplace%20culture%2C%20cohesiveness%2C%20communication%2C%20and%20training%20and%20mentoring%20of%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenvoy.com%2Fcontent%2Fdatareport%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20research%20from%20Envoy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2080%25%20of%20bosses%20regret%20their%20initial%20return-to-office%20plans%2C%20noting%20how%20they%20made%20these%20decisions%20without%20much%20awareness%20of%20office%20attendance%20and%20amenities%20usage.%20The%20risk%20of%20losing%20top%20talent%20has%20kept%20some%20companies%20on%20their%20toes%20about%20adopting%20stricter%20mandates%2C%20and%20the%20Envoy%20study%20further%20suggests%20a%20disconnect%20between%20what%20leaders%20and%20employees%20feel%20about%20return-to-office%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20to%20mention%2C%20mandatory%20return-to-office%20policies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-remote-work-from-home-commute-companies-climate-2023-8%5C%22%3Ecould%20exacerbate%20the%20climate%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20could%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20US%20economy%20down%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20era%20of%20micromanagement%20is%20over%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20Done%20about%20five%20months%20to%20find%20a%20new%20job.%20He%20didn't%20want%20a%20hybrid%20or%20in-person%20position.%20With%20two%20kids%20at%20home%2C%20the%20flexibility%20of%20remote%20work%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0coupled%20with%20no%20commute%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20boon.%20When%20he%20finally%20landed%20his%20new%20role%2C%20it%20was%20worth%20the%20wait.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20quality%20of%20the%20work-life%20balance%20is%20unbeatable.%20It's%20truly%20unbeatable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20his%20new%20role%20and%20firm%2C%20Done%20said%20he%20has%20the%20freedom%20to%20get%20his%20work%20done%20on%20his%20own%20terms.%20There%20are%20still%20meetings%20and%20regular%20training%2C%20and%20everyone%20is%20engaged.%20But%20there's%20no%20micromanagement%20and%20nobody%20telling%20him%20to%20get%20into%20the%20office%20so%20his%20work%20can%20be%20watched%20over%20%E2%80%94%20or%20what%20Microsoft%20calls%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaders-dont-trust-remote-employees-are-productive-microsoft-study-2022-9%5C%22%3Eproductivity%20paranoia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20leaders%20don't%20trust%20their%20workers%20are%20actually%20getting%20stuff%20done.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20been%20in%20a%20work%20from%20home%20environment%20for%20going%20on%20four%20years%20now%2C%20it's%20become%20just%20kind%20of%20second%20nature%20that%20you've%20got%20to%20take%20ownership%20of%20doing%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20company%20that%20really%20embraces%20those%20values%2C%20it%20actually%2C%20I%20think%2C%20drives%20productivity%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20just%20overall%20employment%20satisfaction%20%E2%80%94%20drastically%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20even%20as%20the%20labor%20mar