ious%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CArticle%20370%20was%20called%20temporary%20when%20enacted%20because%20at%20the%20time%2C%20in%201949%2C%20it%20was%20uncertain%20whether%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20India%20at%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ramakrishnan%20explained.%20She%20said%20that%20it%20was%20viewed%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctemporary%E2%80%9D%20until%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20political%20and%20constitutional%20links%20with%20India%20weren%E2%80%99t%20permanent.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20that%20changed%20in%201954%20when%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20passed%20a%20unanimous%20resolution%20ratifying%20the%20accession%20and%20five%20years%20later%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20was%20adopted%20which%20declared%20that%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20irrevocably%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20India%2C%20Nitya%20Ramakrishnan%20argued.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98impugned%20orders%E2%80%99%20(the%20series%20of%20orders%20that%20preceded%20Article%20370%E2%80%99s%20abrogation)%20%E2%80%9Care%20an%20assault%20on%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20itself%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20on%20the%20integration%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20with%20the%20Indian%20Union%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-hearing-day-9-extreme-examples-extreme-cases%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%20Hearing%3A%20SC%20Told%20Extreme%20Examples%20Are%20Necessary%20To%20Solve%20Extreme%20Cases%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamakrishnan%20argued%20that%20only%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20that%20was%20directly%20elected%20by%20the%20people%20of%20the%20region%20could%20recommend%20abrogation%20or%20modification%20of%20Article%20370%20which%20it%20had%20chosen%20not%20to%20do.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20State%20Constituent%20Assembly%20therefore%20recommended%20integration%20with%20India%2C%20with%20Article%20370%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20continuing%20to%20govern%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20accession%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9Cevisceration%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20downgrade%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20status%E2%80%9D%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Csolemn%20bilateral%20pact%20between%20the%20Indian%20Union%20and%20the%20people%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%20through%20unilateral%20declarations%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20the%20people%20of%20the%20state%20had%20no%20say%20in.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20that%20this%20was%20akin%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cagent%20strangling%20the%20principal%20and%20asking%20the%20court%20to%20treat%20it%20as%20suicide%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamakrishnan%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fprocess-erasing-will-of-people-of-jk-with-mala-fide-intent-can-never-legitimately-affect-article-370-nitya-ramakrishnan-on-day-9-of-article-370-hearings%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20vital%20difference%20between%20%E2%80%98integration%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98control%E2%80%99%2C%20linking%20the%20difference%20to%20the%20essence%20of%20Indian%20democracy.%20%E2%80%9CIntegration%20is%20not%20a%20measure%20of%20how%20much%20control%20the%20Centre%20has.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20function%20of%20Central%20control%20or%20power.%20It%20would%20be%20wrong%20to%20say%20that%20people%20in%20Union%20territories%20are%20more%20integrated%20than%20people%20in%20a%20Schedule%20VI%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20%E2%80%9Cis%20not%20how%20our%20democracy%20works.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChain%20of%20proxies%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamakrishnan%20outlined%20the%20process%20of%20how%20a%20chain%20of%20ratifications%20was%20done%20by%20%E2%80%9Cproxy%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cchanging%20of%20meanings%E2%80%9D%20that%20preceded%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370.%20%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20a%20non-existent%20State%20Legislature%2C%20and%20later%20the%20Governor%2C%20the%20President%2C%20and%20Parliament%2C%20in%20quick%20succession%2C%20became%20the%20chain%20of%20proxies%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9CConstituent%20Assembly%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Farticle-370-supreme-court-day-8%5C%22%3EArticle%20370%20Hearing%20in%20SC%3A%20Petitioners%20Question%20Conversion%20of%20State%20Into%20a%20UT%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20this%20was%20engineered%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20Governor%20who%20had%20no%20power%20to%20concur%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20Council%20of%20Ministers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Krishnan%20argued%2C%20adding%20that%20such%20a%20governor%20is%20not%20recognised%20by%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20said%20that%20a%20mere%20amendment%20in%20an%20interpretation%20clause%2072%20years%20later%20cannot%20equate%20any%20other%20body%20with%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20simply%20by%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmajority%20vote%20in%20Parliament%20managed%20by%20a%20party%20in%20power%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EState%20government%E2%80%99s%20consent%20insufficient%20to%20change%20Article%20370%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERamakrishnan%20argued%20that%20since%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20ceased%20to%20exist%20in%201957%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20existing%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%20this%20power%20cannot%20be%20contrived%20through%20Article%20368%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELiveLaw%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20will%20of%20the%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20is%20integral%20to%20the%20mode%20of%20governance%20specified%20in%20Article%20370.%20A%20process%20which%20systematically%20with%20mala%20fide%20intent%20erased%20the%20will%20of%20people%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20can%20never%20legitimately%20affect%20Article%20370%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20was%20quoted%20by%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20LiveLaw%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurther%2C%20Ramakrishnan%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fprocess-erasing-will-of-people-of-jk-with-mala-fide-intent-can-never-legitimately-affect-article-370-nitya-ramakrishnan-on-day-9-of-article-370-hearings%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeliberated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20why%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20in%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGovernor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20was%20imposed%20on%20June%2020%2C%202018%2C%20because%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20withdrew%20from%20the%20coalition%20government%20with%20the%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELiveLaw%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20governor%20dissolved%20the%20assembly%20soon%20after%20even%20though%20the%20National%20Conference%20and%20PDP%20were%20willing%20to%20form%20a%20government%20and%20had%20the%20majority%20along%20with%20other%20small%20parties%2C%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20earthly%20reason%20did%20the%20governor%20have%20to%20dissolve%20the%20house%20within%2030%20minutes%20of%20two%20political%20parties%20saying%20that%20they%20were%20ready%20to%20form%20a%20government%3F%E2%80%9D%20Ramakrishnan%20was%20quoted%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELiveLaw%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20saying.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C