bers%20with%20an%20enhanced%20financial%20incentive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERishi%20Sunak%2C%2043%2C%20told%20the%20parliamentary%20watchdog%20that%20he%20had%20declared%20the%20interest%20on%20the%20Ministerial%20Register%20and%20Greenberg%20concluded%20that%20he%20was%20satisfied%20that%20Rishi%20Sunak%20had%20confused%20the%20concept%20of%20registration%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20declaration%20of%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20formed%20the%20view%20that%20the%20failure%20to%20declare%20arose%20out%20of%20this%20confusion%20and%20was%20accordingly%20inadvertent%20on%20the%20part%20of%20Mr%20Sunak%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20Greenberg%20in%20his%20inquiry%20report%20released%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20view%20of%20this%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20conclude%20my%20inquiry%20by%20way%20of%20the%20rectification%20procedure%20available%20to%20me%20under%20Standing%20Order%20No.%20150%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20which%20stops%20short%20of%20a%20formal%20report%20to%20be%20tabled%20with%20members%20of%20Parliament%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20to%20determine%20a%20course%20of%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20requirements%20of%20the%20Standing%20Order%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20acknowledged%20and%20apologised%20for%20the%20breach%20of%20the%20rules.%20%26quot%3BI%20apologise%20for%20these%20inadvertent%20errors%20and%20confirm%20acceptance%20of%20your%20proposal%20for%20rectification%2C%26quot%3B%20Rishi%20Sunak%20wrote%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20Commissioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20welcome%20your%20confirmation%20that%20your%20investigation%20related%20to%20declarations%20of%20interests%3B%20there%20is%20no%20question%20that%20I%20correctly%20registered%20my%20wife's%20shareholding%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20also%20grateful%20that%20during%20our%20helpful%20discussion%2C%20you%20accepted%20that%20my%20response%20during%20the%20Liaison%20Committee%20hearing%20on%20March%2028