ade%2C%20I%20have%20experienced%20accelerated%20growth%20in%20my%20career.%20I%20made%20it%20to%20director%20level%20in%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20all%20started%20with%20my%20initial%20role%20as%20a%20junior%20engineer.%20After%20a%20few%20months%2C%20I%20sought%20a%20more%20challenging%20learning%20experience%2C%20so%20I%20started%20my%20own%20company%2C%20which%20eventually%20failed.%20I%20then%20joined%20a%20new%20startup%20and%20two%20acquisitions%20later%2C%20I%20became%20director%20of%20engineering%20in%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20European%20wearable%20offices%20of%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20my%20journey%20of%20rapid%20growth%2C%20I%20learned%20many%20valuable%20lessons.%20Some%20were%20taught%20by%20mentors%2C%20while%20others%20were%20found%20in%20books%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20knowledge%20came%20from%20learning%20from%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20five%20things%20I%20learned%20%E2%80%94%20I%20hope%20that%20they%20will%20help%20you%20grow%20in%20your%20career%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Debt%20will%20find%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20very%20important%20lesson%20from%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efinance%20world.%20Debt%20can%20be%20your%20ally%20if%20you%20know%20how%20to%20leverage%20it%20or%20it%20can%20ruin%20you%20if%20not%20properly%20managed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20multiple%20non-money-associated%20debts%20that%20you%20may%20encounter%20in%20your%20career.%20Just%20to%20name%20a%20few%20of%20them%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ESleep%20debt%20happens%20when%20you%20stay%20up%20late%20a%20couple%20of%20weeks%20in%20a%20row%2C%20and%20will%20take%20you%20most%20likely%20on%20a%20path%20to%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3ETechnical%20debt%20that%20you%20ignore%20in%20order%20to%20catch%20a%20critical%20release%2C%20then%20another%2C%20then%20another%2C%20until%20you%20break%20the%20entire%20system%20and%20lose%20the%20trust%20of%20your%20customer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EManagement%20debt%20appears%20when%20you%20ignore%20management%20duties%2C%20skip%201%3A1s%2C%20stop%20sharing%20the%20mission%20and%20things%20start%20to%20pile%20up.%20The%20worst%20part%20of%20it%20all%20is%20that%20you%20don't%20even%20realize%20it%20until%20it%20is%20too%20late.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20was%20under%20the%20impression%20that%20if%20I%20had%20a%20tighter%20deadline%2C%20I%20could%20just%20work%20for%20more%20hours%20in%20the%20weeks%20before%20the%20milestone%20and%20make%20it%20and%20then%20continue%20as%20normal%20after%20the%20deadline.%20I%20was%20simply%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20in%20my%20startup%20days%20we%20had%20this%20huge%20launch%20event%20where%20there%20would%20have%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20press%20for%20the%20unveiling%20of%20the%20product.%20We%20pushed%20really%20hard%20the%20weeks%20before%20to%20make%20the%20deadline%20happen%20and%20we%20made%20it.%20The%20after-effects%20were%20that%20the%20team%20was%20really%20underproductive%20the%20weeks%20after%2C%20myself%20included.%20All%20that%20sleep%20deprivation%20and%20stress%20took%20its%20toll.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20take%20the%20month%20before%20and%20the%20month%20after%20the%20deadline%2C%20on%20average%20the%20velocity%20was%20under%20if%20no%20heroics%20were%20involved.%20But%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20outcome%20it%20was%20worth%20it.%20We%20managed%20to%20have%20a%20successful%20launch%20and%20got%20some%20very%20positive%20press%20that%20landed%20us%20more%20sales%20and%20visibility.%20The%20debt%20made%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20debt%20is%20bad%20and%20you%20should%20leverage%20it%2C%20but%20you%20need%20to%20be%20fully%20aware%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20your%20decisions.%20If%20you%20are%20in%20a%20leadership%20position%2C%20make%20sure%20you%20get%20your%20team%20to%20support%20your%20decisions%20and%20not%20sign%20them%20up%20unknowingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Perception%20is%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20the%20hard%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20some%20time%20until%20I%20finally%20understood%20it.%20Also%20don't%20imagine%20I%20figured%20it%20out%20all%20by%20myself.%20My%20manager%20had%20to%20spell%20it%20out%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20teams%20were%20handling%20a%20critical%20project%20that%20was%20on%20a%20hard%20timeline.%20I%20couldn't%20figure%20out%20why%20even%20if%20everything%20was%20on%20a%20good%20path%2C%20there%20was%20still%20a%20sentiment%20that%20things%20were%20not%20going%20well.%20Critical%20meetings%20on%20status%20were%20popping%20up%20on%20the%20calendar%2C%20questions%20were%20raised%20about%20the%20release%20schedule%20and%20all%20of%20this%20was%20creating%20distractions%20for%20me%20and%20my%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20I%20had%20a%20chat%20with%20my%20manager%20about%20this%20and%20I%20asked%20for%20advice%20because%20I%20failed%20to%20understand%20where%20all%20of%20the%20sentiment%20was%20coming%20from.%20The%20project%20was%20at%20risk%20but%20still%20on%20schedule%20with%20a%20good%20confidence%20level%20of%20delivery.%20I%20failed%20to%20understand%20where%20the%20perception%20was%20coming%20from%20so%20I%20was%20ignoring%20it.%20It's%20just%20perception%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20my%20manager%20told%20me%20bluntly%3A%20%26quot%3BDaniel%2C%20perception%20is%20reality%2C%20it's%20just%20how%20it%20is%20and%20you%20need%20to%20manage%20that%20and%20also%20understand%20where%20it%20is%20coming%20from.%20Otherwise%20you%20risk%20all%20the%20good%20work%20to%20be%20for%20nothing%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%20I%20understood%20what%20needed%20to%20be%20done%20and%20that%20I%20was%20not%20setting%20my%20teams%20up%20for%20long-term%20success.%20I%20wasn't%20touching%20all%20stakeholders%20in%20my%20comms%20and%20I%20was%20not%20proactively%20addressing%20their%20worries.%20My%20gap%20in%20communication%20created%20a%20void%20that%20got%20filled%20up%20mostly%20with%20worries%20that%20had%20no%20grounds.%20I%20made%20sure%20that%20I%20did%20a%20better%20job%20at%20communicating%20progress%20and%20touching%20a%20broader%20stakeholder%20group%2C%20answering%20questions%2C%20and%20providing%20full%20visibility%20on%20plans.%20And%20just%20like%20that%2C%20things%20drastically%20improved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeep%20in%20mind%2C%20you%20also%20need%20to%20address%20and%20manage%20the%20perception%20of%20your%20most%20valuable%20stakeholders%2C%20it%20will%20do%20wonders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Choose%20asymmetric%20opportunities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20really%20made%20a%20big%20difference%20early%20in%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20when%20I%20needed%20to%20decide%20between%20staying%20with%20my%20jr.%20software%20engineering%20job%20at%20a%20big%20company%20or%20joining%20a%20risky%20hardware%20startup%20and%20becoming%20their%20first%20employee.%20I%20went%20with%20the%20risky%20startup%2C%20and%20it%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20best%20decision%20for%20me%20back%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20engineer%2C%20I%20am%20very%20rational%20and%20use%20probabilities%20and%20data%20in%20making%20big%20decisions.%20A%20lot%20of%20my%20friends%20were%20surprised%20that%20I%20went%20for%20a%20risky%20startup%2C%20but%20for%20me%2C%20I%20chose%20an%20asymmetric%20opportunity%20that%20had%20manageable%20downside%20and%20unlimited%20upside.%20You%20need%20to%20judge%20a%20decision%20by%20the%20data%20you%20had%20when%20you%20made%20it%20and%20not%20using%20the%20power%20of%20hindsight%2C%20so%20let%20me%20give%20you%20the%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20always%20wanted%20to%20experience%20startups%2C%20so%20joining%20one%20was%20aligned%20with%20what%20I%20wanted.%20The%20downside%20was%20that%20I%20would%20get%20a%2035%25%20pay%20cut%20and%20that%20I%20could%20be%20out%20of%20a%20job%20in%201%20year's%20time.%20The%20upside%20was%20I%20would%20have%20learned%2010x%20more%20things%20than%20in%20my%20previous%20job%2C%20and%20get%20to%20meet%20a%20lot%20of%20startup%20people%20while%20also%20having%20a%20very%20slim%20chance%20of%20becoming%20rich.%20Taking%20into%20account%20my%20personal%20situation%20at%20that%20time%2C%20it%20made%20sense%20to%20join%20the%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20find%20yourself%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20there%20is%20limited%20and%20manageable%20downside%20but%20unlimited%20upside%2C%20then%20congratulations!%20You%20have%20stumbled%20upon%20an%20asymmetrical%20risk%20opportunity%20that%20can%20accelerate%20your%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20You%20can't%20ride%20the%20wave%20forever%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20oversight%20I%20have%20seen%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20making%20that%20ends%20up%20hurting%20their%20careers.%20Usually%2C%20this%20happens%20when%20you%20get%20some%20achievements%20under%20your%20belt%20and%20you%20try%20to%20ride%20them%20forever.%20You%20need%20to%20pay%20careful%20attention%20because%20everything%20has%20a%20due%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20time%20your%20stakeholders%2C%20manager%2C%20job%20changes%20or%20enough%20time%20passes%20by%2C%20you%20need%20to%20prove%20your%20worth%20again.%20What%20you%20have%20done%20in%20the%20past%20may%20get%20you%20good%20grace%2C%20but%20it%20will%20also%20set%20high%20expectations%20for%20the%20future.%20You%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20are%20filling%20and%20surpassing%20those%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20through%20two%20acquisitions%20this%20was%20the%20biggest%20learning%20that%20has%20helped%20me%20continue%20to%20nurture%20my%20career.%20Whenever%20my%20stakeholders%20changed%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20prove%20again%20that%20I%20was%20competent%2C%20trustworthy%2C%20and%20could%20get%20things%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20You%20are%20solely%20responsible%20for%20your%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20manager%2C%20I%20say%20that%20with%20the%20best%20intentions%20possible.%20Good%20managers%20are%20there%20to%20support%20you%2C%20the%20best%20even%20guide%20you%20but%20in%20the%20end%2C%20you%20are%20responsible%20for%20your%20career.%20You%20need%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20you%20want%2C%20put%20in%20the%20work%2C%20learn%20the%20skills%2C%20and%20deliver%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20important%20things%20is%20to%20not%20shy%20away%20from%20career%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20first%20job%2C%20I%20was%20an%20engineer%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20experiment%20with%20a%20leadership%20role%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20talk%20about%20my%20career%20aspirations%20but%20eventually%2C%20I%20did%20it.%20After%20the%20discussion%2C%20my%20manager%20said%20%3Cem%3Eperfect%2C%20when%20an%20opportunity%20comes%20I%20know%20you%20will%20want%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot.%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20far-fetched%20but%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20couple%20of%20weeks%20later%20it%20happened.%20A%20new%20intern%20joined%20our%20team%20and%20I%20was%20designated%20to%20be%20their%20buddy%20for%20guidance%2C%20onboarding%2C%20and%20task%20allocation.%20That%20was%20my%20first%20interaction%20with%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20know%20when%20to%20have%20career%20conversations%20with%20your%20manager%3F%20It's%20simple%2C%20you%20can%20leverage%20your%201%3A1s.%20If%20you%20want%20a%20promotion%2C%20you%20can%20ask%20your%20manager%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20get%20to%20the%20next%20level%20or%20toward%20the%20destination%20you%20have%20in%20mind.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20career%20ladder%2C%20you%20can%20reverse%20engineer%20it%20and%20figure%20out%20what%20skills%20you%20need%20to%20develop.%20Maybe%20you%20need%20to%20show%20leadership%20skills%20or%20maybe%20demonstrate%20command%20of%20a%20new%20technology.%20Get%20your%20manager%20to%20partner%20with%20you%20on%20your%20career%20growth%20and%20they%20will%20most%20likely%20help%20you%20identify%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESometimes%20you%20will%20fail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20best%20way%20to%20avoid%20making%20any%20mistakes%20is%20if%20you%20don't%20play%20the%20game%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20journey%2C%20I%20preferred%20to%20fail%20fast%20but%20also%20learn%20fast.%20If%20you%20are%20going%20on%20an%20accelerated%20growth%20path%20you%20will%20most%20likely%20make%20mistakes.%20The%20faster%20the%20growth%20the%20more%20mistakes%20will%20happen%20but%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20how%20will%20you%20respond%3A%20do%20you%20learn%20from%20them%20and%20try%20again%20and%20again%2C%20every%20time%20getting%20better%20or%20do%20you%20choose%20to%20stop%20playing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20The%20views%20presented%20are%20my%20own%20and%20can't%20be%20attributed%20to%20any%20past%20and%20current%20employers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDaniel%20Rizea%20is%20a%20director%20of%20engineering%20at%20Google%20who%20writes%20about%20management%20and%20leadership%20in%20tech.%20He%20is%20a%20technology%20enthusiast%20and%20former%20startup%20founder.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fengineering-director-at-google-biggest-lessons-learned-tech-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692868441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e641f14c17ff0019bb35b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fengineering-director-at-google-biggest-lessons-learned-tech-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Daniel%20Rizea%20went%20from%20junior%20engineer%20to%20director%20of%20engineering%20in%2010%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Daniel%20Rizea)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2