cess.%20None%20of%20the%20passengers%20were%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221350%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Search%20patterns%20show%20the%205%2C171%20square%20miles%20Coast%20Guard%20responders%20searched%20for%20Ronnie%20Peale%20Jr.%2C%20who%20fell%20overboard%20186%20miles%20east%20of%20Jacksonville%2C%20Florida.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e621b74c17ff0019bb0a0d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESearch%20patterns%20show%20the%205%2C171%20square%20miles%20Coast%20Guard%20responders%20searched%20for%20Ronnie%20Peale%20Jr.%2C%20who%20fell%20overboard%20186%20miles%20east%20of%20Jacksonville%2C%20Florida.%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20illustration%20by%20Joe%20Perez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELocating%20a%20missing%20person%20among%20the%20sprawling%20labyrinth%20of%20bars%2C%20restaurants%2C%20entertainment%20venues%2C%20pools%2C%20and%20staterooms%20that%20make%20up%20these%20floating%20cities%20can%20be%20frustrating%20and%20time-consuming%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20complications%20of%20texting%20and%20calling%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20someone%20survives%20the%20steep%20fall%20and%20avoids%20the%20ship's%20massive%20propeller%20or%20swirling%20wake%2C%20hypothermia%20can%20set%20in%20within%20minutes.%20Unmonitored%20security%20footage%20and%20inconsistent%20safety%20protocols%20make%20the%20chances%20of%20survival%20even%20more%20slim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20the%20large%20gaps%20of%20time%20between%20a%20person%20going%20overboard%20and%20the%20initiation%20of%20rescue%20missions%20are%20one%20of%20the%20main%20reasons%20why%20man%20overboard%20incidents%20are%20so%20deadly.%20The%20longer%20someone%20is%20alone%20in%20the%20open%20ocean%2C%20the%20lower%20the%20chance%20of%20recovery%2C%20Ross%20Klein%2C%20a%20cruise%20industry%20researcher%20who%20has%20served%20as%20an%20expert%20witness%20before%20Congress%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftravel%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Fcruise-ship-fall-death%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20The%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOverboard%20situations%20are%20obviously%20upsetting%20events%20for%20many%20%E2%80%94%20and%20although%20they%20are%20rare%2C%20with%20the%20likelihood%20of%20an%20incident%20at%20less%20than%200.000001%25%20%E2%80%94%20we%20take%20our%20responsibility%20to%20provide%20a%20safe%20environment%20for%20guests%20and%20crew%20very%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Carnival%20Corporation%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20virtually%20impossible%20to%20fall%20off%20a%20cruise%20ship%20without%20a%20purposeful%20action%20to%20climb%20up%20and%20over%20safety%20rails%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20must%20be%20at%20least%2042%20inches%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegislation%20without%20regulation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224928%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22In%20this%20handout%20from%20the%20U.S.%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20the%20cruise%20ship%20Carnival%20Triumph%20sits%20idle%20February%2011%2C%202013%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico.%20According%20to%20the%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20the%20ship%20lost%20propulsion%20power%20February%2010%2C%20after%20a%20fire%20broke%20out%20in%20the%20engine%20room.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e52fdb912f290019a92df9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Coast%20Guard%20does%20not%20check%20for%20man-overboard%20image%20capture%20or%20detection%20technology%20during%20compliance%20inspections%20of%20cruise%20ships.%3Cp%3E(Photo%20by%20Paul%20McConnell%2FU.S.%20Coast%20Guard%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20prevent%20overboard%20fatalities%2C%20Congress%20in%202010%20required%20cruise%20ships%20to%20integrate%20technology%20%26quot%3Bthat%20can%20be%20used%20for%20capturing%20images%20of%20passengers%20or%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edetecting%20passengers%20who%20have%20fallen%20overboard%2C%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20such%20technology%20is%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Cruise%20Vessel%20Security%20and%20Safety%20Act%2C%20or%20CVSSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Coast%20Guard%20interprets%20the%20statute%20to%20mean%20cruise%20ships%20have%20the%20option%20to%20choose%20between%20image-capture%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20like%20CCTV%20security%20cameras%20%E2%80%94%20or%20detection%20systems%2C%20which%20use%20technology%20like%20thermal%20cameras%20and%20radar%20to%20alert%20crew%20of%20someone%20falling%20overboard%20in%20real%20time%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20agency%20told%20Insider.%20This%20gives%20cruise%20companies%20the%20flexibility%20to%20decide%20which%20type%20of%20technology%20they%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20law's%20vague%20language%20opens%20it%20up%20to%20a%20second%20interpretation%2C%20which%20some%20experts%20say%20was%20the%20original%20intent%20of%20Congress%3A%20that%20cruise%20ships%20are%20allowed%20to%20use%20image%20capture%20technology%20like%20CCTV%20cameras%20to%20fulfill%20the%20CVSSA%20until%20reliable%20man%20overboard%20detection%20technology%20becomes%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Coast%20Guard%2C%20the%20agency%20tasked%20with%20ensuring%20cruise%20ships%20comply%20with%20the%20law%2C%20does%20not%20enforce%20either%20requirement%20because%20the%20rulemaking%20process%20it%20first%20began%20eight%20years%20ago%20is%20not%20yet%20finished%2C%20a%20Coast%20Guard%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%20That%20means%20for%20the%2010-plus%20years%20the%20CVSSA%20has%20been%20law%2C%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dco.uscg.mil%2FPortals%2F9%2FDCO%2520Documents%2F5p%2FCG-5PC%2FCG-CVC%2FPolicy%2520Letters%2F2011%2FCG-543_pol11-09.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehasn't%20inspected%20cruise%20ships%20for%20any%20MOB%20technology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cameras%20or%20otherwise%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENor%20does%20the%20agency%20regulate%20or%20set%20standards%20for%20the%20technology%20cruise%20ships%20should%20use%20to%20detect%20passengers%20who%20have%20fallen%20overboard%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%20However%2C%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20does%20examine%20cruise%20ships%20to%20ensure%20they%20%26quot%3Bhave%20adequate%20procedures%20in%20place%20to%20recover%20a%20man%20overboard%20in%20a%20satisfactory%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20many%20of%20us%20don't%20realize%20that%20about%20any%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Jamie%20Barnett%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20International%20Cruise%20Victims%20Association%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20just%20get%20passed%20and%20then%20happen%20%E2%80%94%20it%20takes%20oversight.%20It%20takes%20people%20paying%20attention%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20it%20happens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMost%20cruise%20ships%20rely%20on%20security%20cameras%20to%20spot%20people%20who've%20gone%20overboard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20Cruise%20Line%20International%20Association%20members%20comply%20with%20the%20requirements%20in%20the%20CVSSA%2C%20with%20most%20ships%20opting%20for%20technology%20that%20is%20capable%20of%20capturing%20images%20of%20people%20falling%20overboard%2C%20a%20CLIA%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20victims'%20advocates%20say%20security%20cameras%20on%20their%20own%20aren't%20an%20effective%20way%20to%20prevent%20man-overboard%20fatalities%20because%20they%20are%20not%20constantly%20monitored.%20And%20since%20cameras%20don't%20always%20capture%20every%20area%20of%20the%20ship%2C%20sometimes%20there's%20no%20footage%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%2029-year-old%20James%20Michael%20Grimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fman-survived-fall-off-cruise-ship-because-things-went-perfectly-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewent%20overboard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20Carnival%20cruise%20ship%20in%20November%202022%2C%20his%20stepsister%20was%20informed%20by%20a%20security%20officer%20that%20they%20had%20footage%20of%20Grimes%20leaving%20the%20bar%2C%20but%20not%20of%20him%20going%20overboard%2C%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Ftravel%2Fcruises%2F2023%2F02%2F22%2Fcruise-ship-overboard-detection-system%2F11172790002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etold%20USA%20Today%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20Carnival%20spokesperson%20told%20the%20outlet%20at%20the%20time%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20cameras%20%26quot%3Bmay%20not%20have%20100%25%20visibility%26quot%3B%20on%20some%20areas%20of%20its%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20Royal%20Caribbean%20crew%20member%20went%20overboard%20the%20Vision%20of%20the%20Seas%20in%202017%2C%20a%20Bahamian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bahamasmaritime.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2FBMA-Investigation-Report-Suicide-onboard-Vision-of-the-Seas.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emarine%20safety%20investigation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20determined%20a%20%26quot%3Bclear%20view%20of%20crewmember%20jumping%20overboard%20was%20not%20detected%20as%20the%20area%20was%20not%20covered%20by%20CCTV%20(blind%20area).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20Insider%2C%20CLIA%20emphasized%20that%20safety%20and%20security%20are%20a%20top%20priority%20for%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20cruise%20lines%20use%20a%20variety%20of%20measures%20to%20maintain%20a%20safe%20environment%20on%20board%20cruise%20ships%2C%20including%20physical%20barriers%20around%20the%20periphery%20of%20external%20decks%20and%20balconies%2C%20video%20surveillance%20systems%20in%20public%20areas%2C%20and%20trained%20crew%20members%20who%20can%20respond%20quickly%20to%20an%20unsafe%20situation%20or%20emergency%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAutomatic%20detection%20systems%20are%20still%20being%20tested%20to%20meet%20international%20standards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mobtronic%20man%20overboard%20system%20testing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e530f44c17ff0019baa15a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20order%20for%20a%20man-overboard%20detection%20system%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20ISO%2C%20it%20must%20have%20a%2095%25%20detection%20success%20rate%20and%20trigger%20no%20more%20than%20one%20false%20alarm%20per%20day.%20Tests%20are%20performed%20using%20dummies%20like%20the%20one%20pictured%20here.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20MARSS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cruise%20industry%2C%20which%20says%20it's%20been%20testing%20man-overboard%2C%20or%20MOB%2C%20detection%20systems%20since%20as%20early%20as%202006%2C%20says%20that%20technology%20that%20senses%20someone%20going%20overboard%20and%20alerts%20crew%20members%20in%20real%20time%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.regulations.gov%2Fcomment%2FUSCG-2016-0492-0006%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eis%20not%20yet%20reliable%20in%20marine%20environments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20nor%20widely%20commercially%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20said%20three%20providers%20had%20demonstrated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23925050-20171030technology-detecting-overboard-passengers%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Binitial%20feasibility%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20it%20recommended%20waiting%20to%20pass%20further%20regulations%20until%20an%20international%20standard%20was%20developed%20so%20as%20to%20not%20%26quot%3Badd%20burden%20to%20industry%20and%20business%20processes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20the%20International%20Standardization%20Organization%20has%20developed%20technical%20requirements%20for%20systems%20to%20detect%20a%20person%20who%20has%20gone%20overboard%20from%20a%20ship.%20The%20standards%2C%20created%20with%20input%20from%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20and%20cruise%20industry%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iso.org%2Fstandard%2F76051.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20a%20Coast%20Guard%20spokesperson%20said%20it's%20not%20aware%20of%20any%20products%20that%20currently%20meet%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarss%2C%20a%20global-technology%20company%2C%20said%20it%20has%20created%20a%20product%2C%20called%20MOBtronic%2C%20that%20is%20on%20track%20to%20meet%20international%20standards%20by%20the%20beginning%20of%202024.%20The%20system%20completed%20120%20tests%20with%20a%20100%25%20success%20rate%2C%20the%20company%20said%2C%20and%20would%20cost%20about%20%24500%2C000%20per%20ship%20to%20install.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20Collier%2C%20a%20program%20lead%20for%20MOBtronic%2C%20said%20the%20technology%20is%20already%20installed%20on%20one%20major%20cruise%20line's%20entire%20fleet%2C%20though%20he%20declined%20to%20specify%20which.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECLIA%20said%20once%20certified%20detection%20systems%20are%20available%2C%20it%20may%20take%20several%20years%20to%20see%20a%20significant%20uptake%20in%20the%20new%20technology%20due%20to%20limited%20shipyard%20and%20product%20availability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Carnival%20Corporation%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bdespite%20the%20claims%20by%20manufacturers%20and%20their%20salespeople%2C%20these%20systems%20are%20still%20unreliable%2C%20as%20was%20the%20case%20when%20our%20company%20piloted%20some%20of%20the%20proposed%20technologies.%26quot%3B%20MOB-detection%20technology%20does%20not%20prevent%20someone%20from%20climbing%20over%20the%20safety%20rails%20or%20jumping%20off%2C%20Carnival%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAfter%20eight%20years%20of%20regulatory%20limbo%2C%20C%3Cstrong%3Eongress%20wants%20answers%20from%20the%20Coast%20Guard%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22MOBtronic%20testing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e62242912f290019a995c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMOBtronic%20has%20passed%20phase%201%20and%20phase%202%20testing%20required%20to%20meet%20the%20ISO%20standard%20and%20expects%20to%20complete%20the%20final%20phase%20by%20the%20beginning%20of%202024.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20MARSS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20eight%20years%20of%20regulatory%20limbo%2C%20lawmakers%20want%20to%20know%20when%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20will%20enforce%20the%20man%20overboard%20technology%20requirements%20of%20the%20CVSSA%20and%20if%20it%20will%20require%20detection%20systems%20on%20every%20ship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20four%20members%20of%20Congress%2C%20including%20Sen.%20Richard%20Blumenthal%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blumenthal.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2F05092023uscoastguardmanoverboarddetectiontechnologyletter.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esent%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Coast%20Guard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20requesting%20information%20about%20the%20current%20use%20of%20man-overboard%20technology%20on%20cruise%20ships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F23925016-20230607-coast-guard-response-re-man-overboard-technology-on-cruise-vessels%3Fresponsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresponse%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20said%20it%20began%20the%20rulemaking%20process%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20agency%20to%20enforce%20the%20requirements%20back%20in%202015%2C%20but%20the%20rule%20was%20never%20finalized%20because%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.regulations.gov%2Fcomment%2FUSCG-2016-0492-0003%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epublic%20comments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bquestioned%20whether%20man-overboard%20detection%20technology%20was%20sufficiently%20reliable%20or%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECollier%2C%20who%20was%20Carnival%20Corporation's%20man-overboard-detection%20expert%20prior%20to%20his%20role%20at%20MOBtronic%2C%20said%20the%20lack%20of%20concrete%20regulation%20from%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20is%20the%20reason%20cruise%20lines%20haven't%20fully%20committed%20to%20installing%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20there%20remains%20no%20clarity%20from%20the%20regulators%2C%20cruise%20lines%20will%20revert%20to%20making%20investment%20decisions%20based%20primarily%20on%20revenue%20generation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Coast%20Guard%20spokesperson%20said%20there%20are%20no%20regulations%20preventing%C2%A0cruise%20lines%20from%20installing%20MOB%20detection%20systems%20on%20their%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Coast%20Guard%20is%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reginfo.gov%2Fpublic%2Fdo%2FeAgendaViewRule%3FpubId%3D202304%26RIN%3D1625-AB91%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20scheduled%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20introduce%20a%20revised%20version%20of%20the%202015%20proposed%20rule%20in%20June%202024%2C%20which%20would%20clarify%20definitions%2C%20update%20existing%20regulations%2C%20and%20create%20performance%20standards%20for%20implementing%20the%20CVSSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Coast%20Guard%20is%20considering%20the%20best%20approach%20to%20address%20this%20issue%20as%20quickly%20as%20practicable%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Blumenthal%20has%20introduced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.blumenthal.senate.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress%2Frelease%2Fblumenthal-and-himes-introduce-bicameral-legislation-to-strengthen-cruise-passenger-safety-laws%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20legislation%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20said%20would%20ease%20some%20of%20the%20original%20act's%20opacity%20by%20requiring%20cruise%20ships%20to%20install%20technology%20that%20can%20both%20capture%20images%20of%20and%20detect%20a%20passenger%20going%20overboard%2C%20a%20change%20CLIA%20said%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bpre-mature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongress%20intended%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20to%20have%20%E2%80%94%20and%20use%20%E2%80%94%20the%20power%20to%20safeguard%20passengers%20more%20effectively%20by%20requiring%20technology%20that%20detects%20people%20going%20overboard%20in%20real%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20shared%20with%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BLegislation%20would%20make%20this%20authority%20absolutely%20clear%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20Coast%20Guard%20regulations%20immune%20from%20any%20future%20attempts%20to%20weaken%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoved%20ones%20navigate%20the%20murky%20waters%20of%20a%20death%20at%20sea%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223596%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ronnie%20Peale%20Jr.%20%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e531b1912f290019a92e63%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222697%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BHe%20trekked%20the%20mountain%20behind%20our%20house.%20The%20land%20was%20his%20comfort%20zone%2C%20fishing%2C%20hiking%2C%20climbing%20trees%2C%20racing%20with%20his%20dogs%20Mylo%20and%20Rocky%2C%26quot%3B%20Linda%20Peale%20wrote%20of%20her%20son.%20%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Linda%20Peale%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJennilyn%20Blosser%2C%20Peale's%20partner%2C%20said%20the%20most%20frustrating%20part%20about%20the%20process%20was%20how%20long%20it%20took%20for%20Carnival%20to%20locate%20the%20video%20footage%20and%20confirm%20that%20Peale%20had%20fallen%20overboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlosser%20said%20her%20family%20told%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecustomer%20service%20around%202%20p.m.%20on%20Monday%2C%20May%2029%2C%20that%20they%20were%20unable%20to%20locate%20Peale.%20The%20employee%20then%20checked%20the%20group's%20bar%20tab%20and%20said%20Peale%20had%20recently%20ordered%20a%20drink%20on%20deck%2010%2C%20she%20said%2C%20which%20led%20the%20family%20to%20believe%20he%20was%20still%20on%20the%20ship.%20Blosser%20said%20she%20later%20found%20out%20her%20cousin%20ordered%20the%20drink%2C%20not%20Peale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%205%20p.m.%2C%20Blosser%20said%20she%20reported%20Peale%20missing%20to%20customer%20service%20a%20second%20time%20after%20he%20didn't%20show%20up%20to%20dinner.%20Carnival%20then%20conducted%20an%20onboard%20search%20and%20announced%20his%20name%20over%20the%20ship's%20loudspeaker%2C%20she%20said.%20The%20cruise%20line%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news.uscg.mil%2FPress-Releases%2FArticle%2F3412515%2Fcoast-guard-suspends-search-for-missing-cruise-ship-passenger-near-florida%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econtacted%20the%20Coast%20Guard%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%206%3A36%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20don't%20know%20why%20it%20took%20so%20long%20for%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20figure%20it%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Carnival%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company's%20internal%20investigation%20%26quot%3Bgives%20a%20different%20set%20of%20facts%20and%20sequence%20of%20events%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20declined%20to%20give%20details%20citing%20%26quot%3Brespect%20for%20his%20family.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20answers%20didn't%20get%20any%20easier%20after%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20suspended%20its%20search%20for%20Peale%2C%20his%20mother%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20cruise%20line%20agreed%20to%20show%20her%20and%20her%20husband%20the%20ship's%20security%20footage%20of%20their%20son%20after%20she%20hired%20a%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20emailed%20the%20Coast%20Guard%20questions%20about%20the%20details%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20such%20as%20what%20time%20Carnival%20viewed%20the%20security%20footage%20and%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20water%20when%20Peale%20fell%2C%20a%20Coast%20Guard%20attorney%20said%20the%20only%20way%20he%20could%20share%20the%20requested%20information%20was%20if%20she%20submitted%20a%20Freedom%20of%20Information%20Act%20request%2C%20according%20to%20emails%20viewed%20by%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiling%20a%20claim%20against%20a%20cruise%20line%20is%20one%20of%20the%20only%20ways%20for%20family%20members%20to%20obtain%20information%20about%20overboard%20incidents%2C%20Barnett%20of%20the%20ICVA%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20lawyers%20won't%20take%20cases%20involving%20cruise%20ship%20fatalities%20because%20the%20complexities%20of%20maritime%20law%20make%20successful%20outcomes%20so%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20a%20cruise%20passenger%20dies%20beyond%20three%20nautical%20miles%20of%20US%2C%20legal%20action%20and%20compensation%20is%20limited%20by%20the%20Death%20on%20the%20High%20Seas%20Act%2C%20or%20DOHSA%2C%20a%20federal%20law%20enacted%20in%201920%20that%20allows%20only%20financially%20dependent%20relatives%20of%20the%20deceased%20to%20file%20a%20wrongful-death%20claim%20for%20monetary%20losses.%20DOHSA%20does%20not%20allow%20survivors%20to%20recover%20damages%20for%20pain%20and%20suffering%20or%20mental%20anguish%2C%20unlike%20other%20wrongful-death%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20Coast%20Guard's%20search-and-rescue%20missions%20for%20cruise%20passengers%20who%20go%20overboard%2C%20American%20taxpayers%20are%20the%20ones%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcoast-guard-does-not-charge-for-search-and-rescue-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efooting%20the%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20not%20cruise%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20financial%20consequence%20when%20someone%20goes%20overboard%20to%20the%20cruise%20line%2C%26quot%3B%20Jim%20Walker%2C%20a%20maritime%20lawyer%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20cruise%20ind