%20set%20to%20begin%20its%20deliberations%20on%20the%20three%20new%20Bills%20that%20seek%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20colonial-era%20criminal%20law%20codes%20in%20India.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20sense%20of%20alarm%20that%20the%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20rush%20the%20Bills%20through%20parliament%20without%20adequate%20consultation%20and%20transparency.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20committee%20whose%20recommendations%20ultimately%20culminated%20in%20the%20present%20form%20of%20the%20Bills%20has%20operated%20in%20complete%20secrecy%20ever%20since%20its%20constitution%20in%20May%202020.%20It%20acquiesced%20to%20the%20involvement%20of%20non-members%20in%20shaping%20the%20recommendations%20for%20the%20Bills%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20(MHA)%20violated%20a%20statutory%20law%20to%20keep%20away%20any%20information%20related%20to%20the%20task.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fparliamentary-committees%2Fhome-affairs%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eschedule%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20standing%20committee%20will%20be%20briefed%20by%20Union%20home%20secretary%20Ajay%20Kumar%20Bhalla%20and%20other%20senior%20MHA%20officers%20from%20Thursday%2C%20August%2024%2C%20until%20Saturday%2C%20setting%20in%20motion%20the%20parliamentary%20scrutiny%20and%20consultation%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%2011%2C%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20monsoon%20session%20of%20parliament%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsedition-law-repealed-three-new-bills-tabled-in-parliament-to-replace-criminal-laws%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eintroduced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20three%20new%20Bills%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%3A%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(BNS)%20Bill%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%3B%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%20(BNSS)%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201898%3B%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakhshya%20Bill%20(BSB)%2C%202023%20to%20replace%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20minister%20requested%20the%20speaker%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20refer%20the%20Bills%20to%20the%20standing%20committee.%20A%20week%20later%2C%20on%20August%2018%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20speaker%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Frajya-sabha-chairman-refers-3-bills-to-replace-ipc-crpc-evidence-act-to-standing-committee-on-home-affairs%2Farticleshow%2F102841636.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereferred%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Bills%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%20on%20home%20affairs%20and%20set%20a%20deadline%20of%20three%20months%20to%20submit%20the%20final%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20supposedly%20bipartisan%20standing%20committee%20is%20headed%20by%20Brijlal%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%20It%20consists%20of%2027%20other%20members%20from%20various%20political%20parties%20of%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20same%20day%20as%20the%20Bills%20were%20referred%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%20(August%2018)%2C%20its%20members%20were%20hastily%20informed%20of%20the%20home%20secretary%E2%80%99s%20three-day%20briefing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20committee%20members%20from%20the%20opposition%20parties%20objected%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cshort%20notice%E2%80%9D%20at%20which%20the%20panel%20is%20meeting%20to%20begin%20deliberations%20and%20requested%20the%20chairman%20to%20push%20the%20dates%20to%20September%20%E2%80%93%20but%20in%20vain.%20The%20original%20schedule%20of%20the%20standing%20committee%20required%20its%20members%20to%20meet%20on%20August%2024%20only%20to%20consider%20and%20adopt%20a%20draft%20report%20on%20%E2%80%9CPrison%20%E2%80%93%20Conditions%2C%20Infrastructure%20and%20Reforms%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20Bills%20have%20provisions%20that%20widen%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20powers%20(introduction%20of%20special%20law%20crimes%20within%20the%20BNS)%2C%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20impact%20free%20speech%20(sedition%20in%20a%20new%20avatar)%2C%20increase%20police%20powers%20(option%20to%20seek%20police%20custody%20from%2015%20to%2040%20or%2060%20days)%20and%20have%20several%20drafting%20errors%20and%20inconsistencies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20one%20common%20theme%20in%20most%20demands%20related%20to%20the%20Bills%20has%20been%20on%20the%20need%20for%20widespread%20consultation%20due%20to%20the%20far-reaching%20implications%20of%20the%20proposed%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOpacity%20in%20the%20crafting%20of%20the%20Bills%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20his%20speech%20introducing%20the%20three%20Bills%2C%20Shah%20claimed%20to%20have%20undertaken%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomprehensive%20consultation%E2%80%9D%20process%20before%20finalising%20the%20proposed%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20claimed%20to%20have%20sought%20views%20from%20%E2%80%9Call%20the%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20Chief%20Justices%20of%20all%20High%20Courts%2C%20law%20universities%2C%20judicial%20academies%2C%20Chief%20Ministers%2C%20Administrators%2C%20Governors%20of%20all%20states%2C%20and%20all%20members%20of%20parliament%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20further%20claimed%20to%20have%20received%20views%20from%20%E2%80%9C18%20states%2C%206%20union%20territories%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%2016%20High%20Courts%2C%205%20judicial%20academies%2C%2022%20Law%20universities%2C%20142%20MPs%2C%20270%20Members%20of%20Legislative%20Assemblies%2C%20and%20the%20public%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20government%20has%20not%20put%20any%20of%20these%20inputs%20or%20views%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENot%20just%20the%20inputs%20of%20the%20stakeholders%2C%20but%20the%20final%20report%20of%20the%20MHA%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcriminallawreforms.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECommittee%20For%20Reforms%20In%20Criminal%20Laws%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(CRCL)%20whose%20recommendations%20ultimately%20culminated%20in%20the%20present%20form%20of%20the%20Bills%20too%20has%20not%20been%20put%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20May%204%2C%202020%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Flawschool%2Fnews%2F3-nlud-professors-part-of-mhas-committee-on-criminal-reforms-156294%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econstituted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20CRCL%20to%20%E2%80%9Crecommend%20criminal%20reforms%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%20The%20committee%2C%20whose%20composition%20changed%20every%20now%20and%20then%2C%20last%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcriminallawreforms.in%2Fmembers%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20Vice-Chancellor%20of%20NLU%20Delhi%20Prof%20Srikrishna%20Deva%20Rao%20as%20its%20chairperson%2C%20registrar%20of%20NLU%20Delhi%20Prof.G.%20S.%20Bajpai%20as%20its%20Member%20and%20Convener%2C%20and%20five%20other%20members.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20important%20nature%20of%20this%20committee%2C%20its%20workings%20have%20been%20absolutely%20secret%2C%20highlighting%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20its%20functioning%20and%20the%20process%20it%20followed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20most%20unfortunate%20that%20the%20MHA%20has%20not%20placed%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20materials%20which%20formed%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20working%20of%20the%20CRCL%20which%20has%20recommended%20significant%20changes%20to%20the%20three%20major%20criminal%20laws%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humanrightsinitiative.org%2Fcontent%2Fdirector%5C%22%3EVenkatesh%20Nayak%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%20India%20office%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECalling%20the%20disclosures%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20requirement%E2%80%9D%2C%20Nayak%20said%20it%20would%20help%20demystify%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20proposed%20Bills.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20will%20help%20people%20debate%20the%20amendments%20in%20an%20informed%20manner%20and%20give%20their%20views%20to%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Home%20Affairs%20which%20is%20vetting%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20he%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECommittee%20conceded%20ground%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20committee%20did%20function%2C%20sources%20within%20the%20establishment%20have%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccrucial%20behind-the-scenes%20role%E2%80%9D%20played%20by%20the%20solicitor%20general%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20and%20the%20additional%20solicitor%20general%20(ASG)%20of%20India%20Suryaprakash%20V.%20Raju%20in%20making%20recommendations%20and%20framing%20the%20three%20Bills.%20All%20this%2C%20despite%20not%20being%20members%20of%20the%20CRCL.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20committee%20had%20to%20concede%20ground.%20That%20is%20what%20the%20ministry%20wanted%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reliable%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERaju%2C%20who%20practised%20at%20the%20Gujarat%20high%20court%20until%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fsv-raju-appointed-additional-solicitor-general-of-sc-6482332%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappointment%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20ASG%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20July%202020%2C%20had%20represented%20Shah%20in%20the%20Sohrabuddin%20encounter%20case.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20CRCL%20who%20spoke%20with%20this%20reporter%20did%20not%20deny%20Mehta%20and%20Raju%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20workings.%20On%20being%20asked%20how%20they%20were%20allowed%20to%20frame%20laws%20despite%20not%20being%20members%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20they%20said%20it%20was%20a%20question%20for%20the%20home%20ministry%20to%20answer.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20asked%20to%20confirm%20if%20the%20CRCL%20conceded%20ground%20to%20Mehta%20and%20Raju%2C%20they%20said%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20having%20discussions%20%5Bwith%20the%20duo%5D.%20Personally%2C%20I%20did%20whatever%20I%20could%20do.%20I%20suppose%20we%20all%20played%20our%20part.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20extent%20of%20influence%20Mehta%20and%20Raju%20%E2%80%93%20both%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20lawyers%20%E2%80%93%20had%20on%20the%20framing%20of%20these%20laws%20can%20only%20be%20known%20if%20and%20when%20the%20records%20of%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20workings%20are%20disclosed.%20Previous%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2Flaw-commission-s-sedition-report-influenced-by-2018-book-that-favours-retention-of-misused-colonial-era-law-648681a8c8941%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereports%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20have%20shown%20how%20government%20bodies%2C%20like%20the%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20have%20disproportionately%20relied%20on%20inputs%20from%20persons%20whose%20opinions%20match%20with%20that%20of%20the%20current%20Union%20government%20%E2%80%93%20instead%20of%20undertaking%20an%20unbiased%20and%20widespread%20consultation%20process.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESecrecy%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20violation%20of%20law%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20secret%20was%20the%20working%20of%20this%20committee%20that%20not%20even%20certain%20applications%20filed%20under%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%20(RTI%20Act)%20were%20entertained%20by%20the%20MHA.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20three%20months%20after%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20CRCL%2C%20this%20reporter%20sought%20information%20on%20eight%20points%20about%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20including%20details%20of%20all%20the%20candidates%20that%20the%20government%20had%20considered%20for%20appointment%20to%20the%20CRCL.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%2C%20because%20there%20were%20concerns%20about%20the%20lack%20of%20representation%20in%20the%20committee%2C%20including%20that%20of%20women%2C%20members%20of%20the%20LGBT%20community%2C%20other%20marginalised%20groups%20and%20civil%20society%20%E2%80%93%20people%20who%20will%20be%20most%20affected%20by%20any%20changes%20in%20these%20criminal%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20RTI%20Act%20stipulates%20a%20time%20frame%20of%2030%20days%20for%20the%20disposal%20of%20an%20RTI%20application%20by%20the%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20and%2045%20days%20for%20the%20disposal%20of%20any%20appeals%20in%20case%20of%20a%20rejection%2C%20or%20an%20unsatisfactory%20or%20no%20response.%20Non-response%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%2025%2C000%20on%20the%20public%20information%20officer%20or%20even%20a%20recommendation%20for%20disciplinary%20action.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%2C%20three%20years%20since%20filing%20the%20RTI%20and%20an%20appeal%20before%20a%20senior%20officer%2C%20along%20with%20multiple%20email%20reminders%20and%20even%20issuing%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20ministry%20seeking%20adherence%20to%20the%20statutory%20timeframe%2C%20no%20information%20about%20the%20CRCL%E2%80%99s%20functioning%20has%20been%20provided.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CReleasing%20the%20CRCL%20materials%20in%20the%20public%20domain%20will%20be%20educational%20for%20the%20citizenry.%20This%20is%20crucial%20also%20because%20the%20Government%20has%20not%20elected%20to%20solicit%20public%20comments%20under%20the%202014%20pre-Legislative%20Consultation%20Policy%20on%20the%20draft%20Bills%20before%20they%20were%20tabled%20in%20Parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Nayak%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20legal%20minds%20fear%20that%20the%20new%20Bills%2C%20without%20wider%20consultations%20from%20experienced%20minds%2C%20would%20erase%20centuries-old%20jurisprudence%20and%20require%20new%20interpretations%20that%20would%20consume%20endless%20court%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CA%20fresh%20litigation%20explosion%20exceeding%20our%20existing%20numbers%20is%20the%20last%20thing%20this%20country%20can%20afford%2C%20but%20this%20appears%20to%20have%20escaped%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20mostly%20non-practising%20eminences%20in%20the%20committee%20set%20up%20for%20this%20exercise%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Abhishek%20Manu%20Singhvi%2C%20senior%20advocate%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F12ft.io%2Fproxy%3Fq%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.hindustantimes.com%252Fopinion%252Fnew-draft-codes-need-wider-consultations-101692193061454.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ESaurav%20Das%20is%20an%20independent%20investigative%20journalist%20and%20tweets%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FOfficialSauravD%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%40OfficialSauravD%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692858913000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F24115637%2FF3-kENLboAAumNv.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20committee%20whose%20recommendations%20ultimately%20culminated%20in%20the%20present%20form%20of%20the%20Bills%20has%20operated%20in%20complete%20secrecy%20ever%20since%20its%20constitution%20in%20May%202020.%20Sources%20told%20The%20Wire%20that%20two%20non-members%20%E2%80%93%20the%20SG%20and%20ASG%20%E2%80%93%20exerted%20influence%20on%20the%20committee.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhow-consultative-was-the-framing-of-the-three-criminal-law-bills-really%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prigozhin%20Presumed%20Dead%20After%20Wagner-Linked%20Media%20Confirms%20He%20Was%20on%20Crashed%20Jet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F24134710%2FScreenshot-2023-06-24-at-1.46.04-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fyevgeny-prigozhin%2Ft-66048326%5C%22%3EYevgeny%20Prigozhin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3Ethe%20founder%20of%20the%20mercenary%20Wagner%20Group%2C%20was%20on%20a%C2%A0business%20jet%20that%20crashed%20in%20Russia%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20Wagner-linked%20media%20said.%20Russian%20aviation%20authorities%20also%20said%C2%A0Prigozhin%20was%20on%20the%20flight.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%2010%20people%20on%20board%20%E2%80%93%20including%20three%20crew%20members%20%E2%80%93%20were%20killed%20in%20the%20crash.%20Eight%20bodies%20were%20found%20at%20the%20crash%20site%20following%20the%20first%20investigations%2C%20Russian%20state%20news%20agency%20RIA%20Novosti%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAccording%20to%20the%20airline%2C%20the%20following%20passengers%20were%20on%20board%20the%20Embraer%20%E2%80%93%20135%20(EBM-135BJ)%20aircraft%3A%E2%80%A6%20Prigozhin%2C%20Yevgeny%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rosaviatsia%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20aviation%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERosaviatsia%20also%20said%20Dmitry%20Utkin%2C%20an%20associate%20of%20Prigozhin%20and%20a%20shadowy%20figure%20who%20managed%20Wagner%E2%80%99s%20operations%2C%20was%20also%20travelling%20on%20the%20plane%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwagner-group%2Ft-64194288%5C%22%3EWagner%3C%2Fa%3E%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWagner-affiliated%20Telegram%20channel%C2%A0Grey%20Zone%C2%A0confirmed%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%C2%A0death%2C%20calling%C2%A0him%20a%20hero%20and%20a%20patriot.%20The%20post%20also%20claimed%20he%20had%20died%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20unidentified%20people%20it%20called%20%E2%80%9Ctraitors%20to%20Russia.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAn%20investigation%20has%20been%20launched%20into%20the%20Embraer%20plane%20crash%20that%20occurred%20tonight%20in%20the%20Tver%20region.%20According%20to%20the%20passenger%20list%2C%20among%20them%20is%20the%20name%20and%20surname%20of%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rosaviatsia%2C%20the%20Russian%20civil%20aviation%20authority%2C%20said%20regarding%C2%A0the%20plane%E2%80%99s%20crashing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jet%20was%20reportedly%20en%20route%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fmoscow%2Ft-19038132%5C%22%3EMoscow%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20St.%20Petersburg%20when%20it%20crashed%20near%20the%20village%20of%20Kuzhenkino%20in%20Tver%2C%20a%20region%20over%20100%20kilometres%20north%20of%20the%20Russian%20capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Embraer%20jet%20model%20has%20only%20recorded%20one%20accident%20in%20over%2020%20years%20of%20service%2C%20and%20that%20was%20not%20related%20to%20mechanical%20failure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20may%20well%20be%20that%20this%20crash%20was%20not%20a%20tragic%20accident%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%20Russia%20bureau%20chief%20Juri%20Rescheto.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20became%20very%20important%20for%20the%20Kremlin.%20He%20became%20so%20powerful%20he%20was%20extremely%20inconvenient%20and%20dared%20to%20publicly%20and%20loudly%20doubt%20the%20sense%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%C2%A0death%20is%20confirmed%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%20imagine%20that%20the%20Wagner%20Group%20will%20no%20longer%20exist%20as%20a%20fighting%20force%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rescheto%20added.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20many%20questions%20about%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%C2%A0whereabouts%20since%20he%20led%20his%20mercenary%20soldiers%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fyevgeny-prigozhins-mutiny-a-stress-test-for-vladimir-putin%2Fa-66048426%5C%22%3Eshort-lived%20mutiny%20against%20Moscow%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20June%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20video%2C%20allegedly%20of%20Prigozhin%2C%20was%20released%20just%20two%20days%20ago%20on%20Telegram%20and%20appeared%20to%20show%20him%20in%20Africa.%20It%20would%20be%20his%20first%20video%20since%20the%20abandoned%20mutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhite%20House%3A%20Prigozhin%E2%80%99s%20death%20%E2%80%98no%20surprise%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20also%20acknowledged%C2%A0the%20news%20and%20President%C2%A0Joe%20Biden%20spoke%20with%20reporters%20candidly%20on%20the%20matter%20as%20he%20was%20leaving%20a%20fitness%20studio%2C%20while%20on%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20for%20a%20fact%20what%20happened%2C%20but%20I%E2%80%99m