rt%20for%20a%20hearing%20and%20transferred%20to%20prison.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20announced%20he%20would%20serve%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20Srettha%20become%20PM%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20consistently%20opposed%20the%20military%2C%20Pheu%20Thai%20made%20a%20commitment%20before%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20election%20not%20to%20form%20a%20coalition%20with%20the%20military-aligned%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20election%2C%20Pheu%20Thai%20initially%20supported%20Move%20Forward%20in%20its%20attempt%20to%20form%20a%20government%2C%20but%20after%20its%20leader%2C%20Pita%20Limjaroenrat%2C%20was%20blocked%20by%20the%20military-appointed%20Senate%20from%20becoming%20prime%20minister%2C%20Pheu%20Thai%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fthailand-pheu-thai-coalition-military-parties-b6d3076f3b237fade491bc6c7ba32856%5C%22%3Echanged%20its%20tune%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20nominated%20its%20own%20prime%20ministerial%20candidate%2C%20Srettha%2C%20a%20wealthy%20property%20developer%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fthailand-new-prime-minister-srettha-thavisin-af1ed439685a703cd1c34abf40ae2876%5C%22%3Epolitical%20newcomer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20formed%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThaiEnquirer%2Fstatus%2F1693607293789855936%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Ecoalition%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20two%20military-aligned%20parties%2C%20the%20Palang%20Pracharath%20Party%20and%20Ruam%20Thai%20Sang%20Chart%20Party%2C%20and%20a%20range%20of%20others.%20This%20gave%20Srettha%20the%20support%20he%20needed%20from%20the%20military-appointed%20senators%20to%20win%20the%20prime%20ministership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Move%20Forward%20and%20Pheu%20Thai%20had%20been%20vocal%20critics%20of%20the%20former%20military-led%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20two%20parties%20had%20different%20stances%20on%20one%20main%20issue%3A%20Thailand%E2%80%99s%20strict%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fexplainer-why-was-the-winner-of-thailands-election-blocked-from-becoming-prime-minister-209730%5C%22%3El%C3%A8se-majest%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%20law%2C%20which%20punishes%20anyone%20who%20criticises%20the%20king%20or%20other%20senior%20royals%20with%20up%20to%2015%20years%20in%20prison.%20Move%20Forward%20pledged%20to%20reform%20it%2C%20while%20Pheu%20Thai%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationthailand.com%2Fthailand%2Fpolitics%2F40027410%5C%22%3Ecommitted%3C%2Fa%3E%20not%20to%20change%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20difference%20was%20likely%20a%20key%20determinant%20in%20Move%20Forward%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20victory%2C%20but%20also%20the%20reason%20why%20military%20and%20conservative%20parties%20have%20now%20been%20willing%20to%20support%20Pheu%20Thai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20significant%20party%20to%20vote%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSaksithCNA%2Fstatus%2F1693959822897811874%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eagainst%3C%2Fa%3E%20Srettha%20in%20the%20parliament%20election%20was%20Move%20Forward%20and%20its%20149%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20secretary-general%20of%20Move%20Forward%20said%20the%20party%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FThaiEnquirer%2Fstatus%2F1693859291638460500%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Eopposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20new%20coalition%20because%20it%20refused%20to%20be%20complicit%20in%20returning%20military-aligned%20parties%20to%20government%2C%20even%20one%20led%20by%20Pheu%20Thai.%20He%20argued%20this%20would%20perpetuate%20the%20notion%20that%20Thailand%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cultimate%20power%E2%80%9D%20belonged%20in%20the%20unelected%20Senate%20rather%20than%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20now%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20no%20coincidence%20that%20Thaksin%20arrived%20on%20the%20day%20his%20party%20returned%20to%20power%2C%20and%20the%20foundations%20are%20already%20being%20set